# Database Models and Operations

## Context
- Applies to all SQLAlchemy models and database operations
- Ensures consistent async database patterns
- Follows repository pattern for data access

## Requirements
- All models must inherit from Base class
- Use appropriate mixins: UUIDMixin, BigIntMixin, TimestampMixin
- Always use async sessions for database operations
- Implement repository pattern for data access
- Use Mapped[] type annotations for all columns
- Handle transactions properly with async context managers
- Use Alembic for all database migrations
- Never access database directly from routes

## Examples
<example>
# Good: Proper model with mixins and repository pattern
from sqlalchemy import String
from sqlalchemy.orm import Mapped, mapped_column
from app.models.base_model import Base, UUIDMixin, TimestampMixin

class User(Base, UUIDMixin, TimestampMixin):
    __tablename__ = "users"
    
    email: Mapped[str] = mapped_column(String(255), unique=True, index=True)
    name: Mapped[str] = mapped_column(String(255))
    is_active: Mapped[bool] = mapped_column(default=True)

# Repository implementation
class UserRepository:
    def __init__(self, session: AsyncSession):
        self.session = session
    
    async def create(self, user_data: dict[str, Any]) -> User:
        user = User(**user_data)
        self.session.add(user)
        await self.session.commit()
        await self.session.refresh(user)
        return user
    
    async def get_by_email(self, email: str) -> User | None:
        result = await self.session.execute(
            select(User).where(User.email == email)
        )
        return result.scalar_one_or_none()
</example>

<example type="invalid">
# Invalid: Synchronous operations without proper typing
class User(Base):
    __tablename__ = "users"
    
    id = Column(Integer, primary_key=True)  # Wrong: Not using Mapped[]
    email = Column(String)  # Wrong: No length specified
    
    @classmethod
    def get_by_email(cls, email):  # Wrong: Synchronous, no repository
        return session.query(cls).filter_by(email=email).first()
</example>